page.title: 01Introduction
page.content: The first things that visitors notice when they come here is the flat land and the absence of the trees . Most of the area is sparsly populated except in the centre of Gedney Hill. The ground around here is low, that is why we have a lot of dykes and drains, for drainage purposes. The roads are parallel,long and straight and the fields are rectangular . There are regular bus services to Peterborough, Spalding and Wisbech. There is a church and opposite is a well-stocked shop. There are three pubs in the area and all are quite old.
